==English==
{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
From {{ME.}} ''[[protesten]]'' < {{OF.}} ''[[protester]]'' < {{L.}} ''[[protestare]]'' < {{L.}} ''[[pro-]]'' "before" + ''[[testare]]'' "to testify" < {{L.}} ''[[testis]]'' "witness".

===Pronunciation===
*(''verb''): prətĕst', /prəˈtɛst/, /<tt>pr@"tEst</tt>/
*{{audio|en-us-protest-verb.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*(''noun''):
**(''[[RP]]''): /ˈprəʊtɛst/, /<tt>"pr@UtEst</tt>/
**(''US''): prō'tĕst, /ˈproʊtɛst/, /<tt>"proUtEst</tt>/
*{{audio|en-us-protest-noun.ogg|Audio (US)}}
[[Category:English heteronyms]]
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛst|-ɛst]]

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-verb}}
# to make a strong [[objection]]
#:''How dare you, I '''protest'''!''
#:''The public took to the streets to '''protest''' over the planned change to the law.''

